member.name: Amy Zhang
member.bio: Amy X. Zhang is an assistant professor at University of Washington's Allen School of Computer Science and Engineering, where she directs the Social Futures Lab. Her research interests are in social computing and HCI.

member.name: Quan Ze (Jim) Chen
member.bio: Quan Ze (Jim) is a former PhD student, now postdoc in SFL. He is interested in understading disagreement and ambiguity in human annotation and building  crowdsourcing and human-in-the loop workflows.

member.name: Xinyi Zhou
member.bio: Xinyi Zhou is a Postdoctoral Scholar at the University of Washington. Her research focuses on developing AI methods (e.g., LLMs, RAG) that leverage multimodal and behavioral data to address societal challenges, ranging from misinformation to human well-being.

member.name: Nick Vincent
member.bio: Nick is a Postdoctoral Scholar working with the Social Futures Lab at UW and the Computational Communication Lab at UC Davis. His research aims to give the public more voice in determing how the AI systems we all contribute data to are used.

member.name: Ruotong Wang
member.bio: Ruotong Wang is a Ph.D. student at University of Washington CSE. She is interested in understanding and developing sociotechnical systems that facilitate communication and collaboration among diverse community members.

member.name: Galen Weld
member.bio: Galen Weld is a PhD student whose work focuses primarily on large-scale analyses of social media platforms' governance and content moderation strategies, with a particular focus on reddit.

member.name: Kevin Feng
member.bio: Kevin is a PhD student in Human Centered Design & Engineering at the University of Washington. His is interested in systems and tools that foster collaboration between diverse stakeholders, particularly within UX design and machine learning workflows.

member.name: Jina Yoon
member.bio: Jina Yoon is a PhD student of Computer Science at the University of Washington. Her current research interests are in fostering empathetic conversation, combating misinformation, and leveraging addictive design for good. She also really likes to play video games.

member.name: Leijie Wang
member.bio: Leijie Wang is a PhD student of Computer Science at the University of Washington. He's interested in content moderation systems that respect people's expectations about privacy and fairness on various online platforms.

member.name: Alicia Guo
member.bio: Alicia is a PhD student at the University of Washington CSE. Her research interests are in creativity support tools and representations of generated content in human-AI systems.

member.name: Inyoung Cheong
member.bio: Inyoung Cheong is a PhD student of Law at the University of Washington. Her research explores AI policy, governance, and regulatory approaches to mitigate foreseeable societal harms and developing interventions that promote accountability.

member.name: Teanna Barrett
member.bio: Teanna (she/her) is a PhD at the University of Washington CSE. She is interested in building data scientists' capacity to reason ethically through their work and challenge Western-centric data ethics paradigms through Black thought.

member.name: Emelia May Hughes
member.bio: Emelia Hughes graduated from UW in June with degrees in Informatics and Drawing & Painting. Her research interests are in human-computer interaction, and she is currently focusing on the UX surrounding credibility. Next fall, she will be a PhD student at Notre Dame.

member.name: Jenny Fan
member.bio: Jenny Fan is a designer and creative technologist interested in reimagining digital civics in the online public sphere. She received her Masters in Design Engineering from Harvard University and B.S. Economics (with a focus on Information Systems) from the University of Pennsylvania, Wharton.

member.name: Peipei Nie
member.bio: Peipei Nie is a social computing researcher from the University of Michigan's School of Information interested in our information ecosystem’s impact on democracy. Her research focuses on content moderation, mis/disinformation and trust, and news and civic engagement with applications to social media and online communities.

member.name: Tony Li
member.bio: Tony (he/him) is a master's student in the HCDE department at the UW. He is also the president of the HCDE Graduate Student Association. WIth industry experience in data engineering, Tony is interested in human-AI interaction and the intersection of data and HCI.

member.name: Simona Liao
member.bio: Simona Liao (she/they) is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying computer science and GWSS (Gender, Women, and Sexuality Studies). She is interested in Virtual Reality platforms and communities, and how to design them against harassments.

member.name: Anson Huang
member.bio: Anson Huang is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying computer science and political science. His research interests are in the intersection of civics and tech.

member.name: Ryan Li
member.bio: Ryan Li is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington majoring in Computer Science and minoring in Data Science. His research interests are in online misinformation and disinformation.

member.name: Andre Ye
member.bio: Andre Ye is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying computer science and philosophy. His primary research interest is in building more robust and responsible machine & deep learning systems.

member.name: Lin Qiu
member.bio: Lin Qiu is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying Computer Science. Her research interests are in human-computer interaction and she is currently working on improving collaboration in small online meetings.

member.name: Shreya Sathyanarayanan
member.bio: Shreya Sathyanarayanan is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying Computer Science. Her research interests are in HCI, designing and developing tools for online collaboration, and addressing misinformation.

member.name: Kianna Bolante
member.bio: Kianna Bolante is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying Computer Science. Her research interests are in human-computer interaction, social computing, and education.

member.name: Sarah Fredrickson
member.bio: Sarah is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying computer science. Her research interests are in content moderation, online communities, and addressing misinformation.

member.name: Pranati Dani
member.bio: Pranati is an undergraduate student at UW studying Computer Science and minoring in Business Administration. She is extremely interested in the connection between communication and education with computing, and is working on the bridge between asynchronous and synchronous communication.

member.name: Lawrence Tan
member.bio: Lawrence Tan is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying Computer Science. His research interests are in human-computer interaction and novel applications of machine learning.

member.name: Bingcan(Gloria) Guo
member.bio: Bingcan(Gloria) Guo is an exchange student at the University of Washington. She is an undergraduate student at The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology studying Data Science and Computer Science. Her research interests are gamification and understanding online communities.

member.name: Judy Kang
member.bio: Judy Kang is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying Computer Science. Her research interests are UX design, HCI and accessibility and inclusive design.

member.name: Khushi Khandelwal
member.bio: Khushi Khandelwal is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying Computer Science. Her research interests are in human-computer interaction, online misinformation, and artificial intelligence.

member.name: Brooke Nelson
member.bio: Brooke Nelson is an undergraduate student at the University of Colorado: Boulder majoring in computer science. Her research interests are to better understand online communities and effective content moderation.

member.name: Kathryn Yurechko
member.bio: Kathryn Yurechko is an undergraduate student at Washington and Lee University studying Computer Science, Philosophy, and Poverty and Human Capability Studies. Her research interests are in content moderation and the support of marginalized communities on social media.

member.name: Anisa Callis
member.bio: Anisa is a rising 4th year at Penn State University in State College, PA studying Human Centered Design and Development. She has done research on visually impaired peoples’ interactions with TikTok, and also groups and their interactions with AI towards better decision-making.

member.name: Philip Baillargeon
member.bio: Philip Baillargeon (he/him) is an undergraduate student at Stanford University studying Computer Science and Human-Computer Interaction. His interests include social computing, neurodiversity in social computing systems, accessible education technology, and public interest technology.

member.name: Andrew Shaw
member.bio: Andrew Shaw (he/him) is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying computer science and philosophy. His resesarch interests are in computer and AI ethics, particularly regarding the impacts of sociotechnical systems on marginalized communities.

member.name: Sydney Kuhl
member.bio: Sydney Kuhl is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying computer science. Her research interests are in machine learning, natural language processing, and online misinformation.
